sentences: Helena Mathilda Munktell (24 November 1852 – 10 September 1919) was a Swedish composer.
She was the youngest of nine children of Henrik Munktell (1804–1861) and Christina Augusta Eggertz (1818-1889).
She was the youngest of nine children of Henrik Munktell (1804–1861) and Christina Augusta Eggertz (1818-1889).
Her sister Emma Josepha Sparre (1851–1913)  was a painter.
Her debut as a composer took place in Sweden in 1885.
In the late 1890s, Helena Munktell began to compose music for orchestra.
In 1915 she became a member of the Royal Swedish Academy of Music and in 1918 she co-founded the Swedish Society of Composers.
